{% block title %}{{ model.title }} : {{ global.site_title }}{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<section class="col-24">
	<h1>{{ model.title }}</h1>	
</section>

<style>
	.highlight	{background-color: red !important;}
</style>

<section class="col-24">
	<section class="col-8 first">

		<div class="js-mul-tabs-example mul-tabs">
			{% include "page-tabs" %}
			<div id="tabs-1">
				<p>
					The Interactive Data Table organizes data on a page or application so it’s easy for the user to view and comprehend. It’s used along with the Mini Filter so users can syphon data to view exactly what they need. Designers can also opt to combine the Interactive Data Table with the Inline Search Container to allow users to search for the data they want to view.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-2">
				<p>
					Use the Interactive Data Table when you want to organize data that the user needs to interact with (search, filter, take clickable actions, etc). 
				</p>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-3">
				<ul>
					<li>The Interactive Data Table works within the <a href="base-grids">Mercer Grid System</a>, which means the sizing is flexible and fluid to adapt to designer’s choices, user devices, and varying screen sizes.</li> 
					<li>Only use the Interactive Data Table in larger page/application foundations, such as the <a href="layout-workspace">Workspace Layout</a>.</li>
					<li>Don’t use the Interactive Data Table in a <a href="container-sidebar">Sidebar Container</a> or <a href="layout-sidebar">Sidebar Layout</a>, unless you only need to display a small amount of data.</li>
				</ul>
				
				<strong>Color</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>Coloring for each row in the Interactive Data Table will adhere to the <a href="base-colors">Mercer Color Pallet</a> for all Data Tables.</li>
					<li>When the user hovers over a specific row, that row will be highlighted in yellow (#FCF8E3).</li>
				</ul>
				
				<strong>Width</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>Designer can set column width using a helper class. Since the Interactive Data Table functions within the Mercer Grid System, it will automatically adapt and configure itself.</li>
				</ul>
				
				<strong>Row Details</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>Padding for Interactive Data Table rows are set to 5 pixels on the top and bottom and 10 pixels to the left and right.</li>
					<li>Line height of Interactive Data Table rows are 13 pixels to keep text consistent with Mercer branding.</li>
					<li>Some rows can be assigned a Right Align Helper Class to alter rows that might not have the same amount of content fields as other rows, such as the Subtotal and Total rows.</li>
					<li>Text will wrap in basic rows to adapt to longer content, but the label rows will stay in the same position, which is vertically aligned to the top of the row.</li>
				</ul>

				<strong>Filters</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>The Interactive Data Table defaults data to an ascending order, but users can change the order of data to descending and vice versa by clicking on the header name.</li> 
					<li>Column headers will be links that user can click on to sort data from ascending to descending and vice versa.</li>   
					<li>The designer can determine what filters the Interactive Data Table will have, like sort by date, alphabetical order, assignment, etc.</li>
					<li>The Interactive Data Table will contain a "Filter" Input Box located at the top right of the table.</li> 
					<li>Users can change the order of the columns by clicking on the appropriate "Filter" link located on the top left of the Interactive Data Table.</li> 
				</ul>

			</div>
			<div id="tabs-4">
				{% include "table-navbar" %}
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="col-24">
			<h4 class="mul-hdr-rule">Dependencies</h4>
			<table class="mul-table mul-table-borders" id="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" title="" summary="">
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th width="" scope="col">Library</th>
						<th width="" scope="col">Location or Download</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>jQuery 1.10.2</td>
						<td>assets/scripts/core_v2/lib/jquery</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>FooTables 2.0</td>
						<td>assets/scripts/core_v2/lib/jquery/plugins</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>FooTables 2.0 - Sorting Plugin</td>
						<td>assets/scripts/core_v2/lib/jquery/plugins</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>FooTables 2.0 - Filter Plugin</td>
						<td>assets/scripts/core_v2/lib/jquery/plugins</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class="col-16">

		<h4 class="mul-hdr-rule">Example</h4>
		
		<!-- INTERACTIVE DATA TABLE - EXAMPLE - BEGINS -->
		<table class="mul-table mul-footable mul-table-borders mul-table-striped mul-table-hover" data-filter="#filter" id="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" title="" summary="">
			<caption>
				<div class="col-19 first">&nbsp;</div>
				<div class="col-5 mul-tbl-data-filter">
					<input id="filter" type="text" placeholder="Filter" tabindex="" title="Type to filter results." />
				</div>
			</caption>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th class="col-1" scope="col"></th>
					<th class="col-6" scope="col"><a href="javascript:;">Task</a></th>
					<th data-sort-initial="ascending" class="col-2" scope="col"><a href="javascript:;">Type</a></th>
					<th class="col-8" scope="col">
						<a href="javascript:;">Client</a> |
						<a href="javascript:;">Location</a>
					</th>
					<th class="col-4" scope="col"><a href="javascript:;">Assigned To</a></th>
					<th class="col-3 mul-nowrap mul-align-right" scope="col"><a href="javascript:;">Start Date</a></th>
					<th class="col-3 mul-nowrap mul-align-right" scope="col"><a href="javascript:;">End Date</a></th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tbody>

				{% for item in global.table_data %}
				<tr>
					<td>{{ item.checkbox }}</td>
					<td>{{ item.task }}</td>
					<td>{{ item.type_global }}</td>
					<td>
						<a href="javascript:;">{{ item.company }}</a> |
						{{ item.location}}
					</td>
					<td>
						{{ item.abbrev_first_name}} {{ item.last_name}}
					</td>
					<td class="mul-nowrap mul-align-right">{{ item.start_date }}</td>
					<td class="mul-nowrap mul-align-right">{{ item.end_date }}</td>
				</tr>
				{% endfor %}
				
			</tbody>
		</table>
